INSERT INTO `Project` VALUES (1,NULL,'Configure Ubuntu in Amazon EC2 Cloud','','completed','1000',14,1,'2011-01-10','2011-01-10','2011-01-20','<div>This project needs creating & configuring amazon AWS EC2 EBS micro instance which is available free of change by amazon. More information at <a href=\"http://aws.amazon.com/free\">http://aws.amazon.com/free</a><br/></div><br/>\r\n\r\n<div>Please make sure that you read all the conditions mentioned on the amazon site to make sure that the instance would not get charged for any resources allocated to it outside the free tier. </div><br/>\r\n\r\n<div>You would be provided with a amazon account with a valid credit card, so that you can login & get started with instance creation & deployment.</div><br/>\r\n\r\n<b>Your deliverables would be as follows\r\n</b><br/><br />\r\n<ul><li>\r\nThe instance need to be running Ubuntu OS. So this is the first task you need to do. You can either pick up a pre-configured Ubuntu instance or can create one from scratch.<b style=\"color: #000;\">If you are picking a pre-configured instance, make sure that the resources the instance is utilizing is well within the free tier usage limit</b></li>\r\n<li>Install ngnix server on the instance.</li> <li>Configure the server so that multiple websites can be hosted on it</li>\r\n<li>Install mysql & PHP on the server & install all the dependencies for it to run with ngnix server</li>\r\n<li>You would be provided with two website dump of <a href=\"www.cofoundersgyan.com\">www.cofoundersgyan.com</a> & <a href=\"www.stalkninja.com\">www.stalkninja.com</a> . Former is in wordpress & latter uses custom html. Both sites use their own database. You need to transfer the dump to the server, configure the respective database & make them work</li>\r\n<li>You need to document all the steps that you follow to do above steps in the progress sheet</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br/>\r\n<div>Once both the sites are working on the instance, the project would be done after reviewing the progress sheet.</div>\r\n','System Administrator,Linux, Web-Server Installation ','Reference Link:\n\n   1. https://help.ubuntu.com/community/EC2StartersGuide\n   2. http://davidwinter.me/articles/2009/06/13/php-and-nginx-the-easy-way/\n   3. http://docs.amazonwebservices.com/AWSEC2/2007-08-29/GettingStartedGuide/\n   4. http://www.rajiv.com/blog/2008/02/04/amazon-ec2/\n   5. http://wiki.nginx.org/VirtualHostExample\n   6. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eZI6URU-Jak\n   7. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4WG_N2DqLQg\n   8. http://rubypond.com/blog/setting-up-nginx-ssl-and-virtual-hosts\n   9. http://paulstamatiou.com/how-to-getting-started-with-amazon-ec2\n  10. https://forums.aws.amazon.com/thread.jspa?threadID=54370&tstart=225\n  11. http://somic.org/2009/09/21/security-groups-most-underappreciated-feature-of-amazon-ec2/\n  12. http://www.linuxhomenetworking.com/wiki/index.php/Quick_HOWTO_:_Ch14_:_Linux_Firewalls_Using_iptables#What_Is_iptables.3F\n  13. https://help.ubuntu.com/community/IptablesHowTo\n  14. http://articles.techrepublic.com.com/5100-10878_11-1047763.html\n  15. http://www.puschitz.com/SecuringLinux.shtml\n  16. http://www.infotechmigrant.com/30/vps-dedicated-centos-nginx-fastcgi-mysql-php-wordpress/\n\n\nProcedure:\n\n    * Installation and configuration of UBUNTU SERVER 10.04\n            * Read Ref. Link https://help.ubuntu.com/community/EC2StartersGuide\n    * Selecting an instance image from (http://uec-images.ubuntu.com/server/lucid/current/ ) in us-east zone. \n\n\nUS-EAST-1 :|: 32-bit :|: EBS :|: ami-a055a4c9\n\n    * After It I run following commands:\n\n\nexport EC2_PRIVATE_KEY=$HOME//pk-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX.pem\n\nexport EC2_CERT=$HOME//cert-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX.pem\n\nexport JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-6-openjdk/\n\n# to generate ec2 keypair\nec2-add-keypair ec2-keypair > ec2-keypair.pem\n\nchmod 600 ec2-keypair.pem\n\n# to deploy a micro instance\nec2-run-instances ami-a055a4c9 -k ec2-keypair.pem -t t1.micro\n\n#to port 22 access\nec2-authorize default -p 22\n\n#then establish connection from ssh\nssh -i /path/to/ec2-keypair.pem ubuntu@\n\n    * Installation and configuration of NGINX WEB SERVER, PHP and MySql \n\n    * Read Ref. Link http://davidwinter.me/articles/2009/06/13/php-and-nginx-the-easy-way/\n    * http://www.howtoforge.com/installing-nginx-with-php5-and-mysql-support-on-ubuntu-8.10\n    * After It I run following commands:\n\n\n## It installes nginx php5-cgi php5-curl etc. Php related things + mysql server etc..\nsudo apt-get install nginx php5-cgi php5-mysql php5-curl php5-gd php5-idn php-pear php5-imagick php5-imap php5-mcrypt php5-memcache php5-mhash php5-ming php5-pspell php5-recode php5-snmp php5-tidy php5-xmlrpc php5-xsl mysql-server mysql-client\n\n            ## At the time of installation mysql asks for setting up root user                 password fill that and confirm that.\n\n    * Follow all steps of  Ref. Link http://davidwinter.me/articles/2009/06/13/php-and-nginx-the-easy-way/\n\n\n    * Installation of WEBMIN         \n\n    * If you like to install and update Webmin via APT, edit the /etc/apt/sources.list file on your system and add the lines\n\ndeb http://download.webmin.com/download/repository sarge contrib\n\ndeb http://webmin.mirror.somersettechsolutions.co.uk/repository sarge contrib\n\n    * You should also fetch and install GPG key with which the repository is signed, with the commands :\n\nwget http://www.webmin.com/jcameron-key.asc\napt-key add jcameron-key.asc\n\n    * You will now be able to install with the commands :\n\n\napt-get update\napt-get install webmin\n\n    * All dependencies should be resolved automatically.\n\n    * Configuration of Virtual Hosts         \n\n    * We have to park two websites thats why we have create two virtual hosts.\n\n\nFirst one for: www.stalkninja.com\nSecond one for: www.cofoundersgyan.com\n\n    * In /etc/nginx/sites-available firstly we have to create two files √¢‚Ç¨≈ìstalkninja.com√¢‚Ç¨¬ù and √¢‚Ç¨≈ìcofoundersgyan.com√¢‚Ç¨¬ù\n\n\nHere is one example for virtualhost configuration for cottonslate.com and cofoundersgyan.com which are pointing to same root\n\nfile:: /etc/nginx/sites-avaiable/cottonslate.com\nserver\n{\n        listen       80;\n           server_name www.cottonslate.com cottonslate.com www.cofoundersgyan.com cofoundersgyan.com;\n\n               root /home/ubuntu/www/cofoundersgyan.com;\n    \n           location /\n           {                \n              index  index.html index.htm index.php;\n           }\n\n   \n           location ~ \\.php$\n          {\n              fastcgi_pass    127.0.0.1:9000;\n              fastcgi_index   index.php;\n              fastcgi_param   SCRIPT_FILENAME /home/ubuntu/www/cofoundersgyan.com$fastcgi_script_name;\n              include         fastcgi_params;\n          }   \n }\n\n\nFor example for creating www.stalkninja.com virtualhost simply create file of the name of stalkninja.com and copy all above example and edit it.\n\nDefine\n\n    * server_name www.stalkninja.com stalkninja.com\n    * root \n    * And again in location ~\\.php$ part edit /home/ubuntu/www/cofoundergyan.com$fastcgi_script_name; to your value $fastcgi_script_name;\n\n\n\nAfter doing all above for enabling website we have simply create a link in /etc/nginx/sites-enabled using ln command and reload the configuration of nginx web server using following command\n\nsudo /etc/init.d/nginx reload\n\n    * Copying files to server\n         \n    * We use command scp\n    * scp -i ec2-keypair.pem -r  ubuntu@ec2-184-73-237-41.compute-1.amazonaws.com:\n    * Above command copy all files of directory inside it to remote host recursively (-r) option..\n\n\n\n    * Setting Database for cofoundersgyan.com and stalkninja.com using webmin            \n\n    * Using WEBMIN I have create √¢‚Ç¨≈ìcofoundersgyan√¢‚Ç¨¬ù user.\n    * Create a database of same name\n    * Give all permissions\n    * After all above click in cofoundersgyan database link and click in execute SQL link there is another option for import text file using this we can add our database backup to mysql. \n\n    * Setting Up WORDPRESS in NGINX WEB SERVER\n\n\nRef. Link http://www.infotechmigrant.com/30/vps-dedicated-centos-nginx-fastcgi-mysql-php-wordpress/\n\nfile:: /etc/nginx/sites-avaiable/cottonslate.com\nserver {\n\n   listen       80;\n   server_name www.cottonslate.com cottonslate.com www.cofoundersgyan.com cofoundersgyan.com;\n\n   root /home/ubuntu/www/cofoundersgyan.com;    \n\n   location / {                \n\n       index  index.html index.htm index.php;\n\n    # this serves static files that exist without running other rewrite tests\n    if (-f $request_filename) {\n        expires 30d;\n        break;\n    }\n    # this sends all non-existing file or directory requests to index.php\n    if (!-e $request_filename) {\n        rewrite ^(.+)$ /index.php?q=$1 last;\n    }\n    }\n       location ~ \\.php$ {\n                  fastcgi_pass    127.0.0.1:9000;\n                  fastcgi_index   index.php;\n                  fastcgi_param   SCRIPT_FILENAME /home/ubuntu/www/cofoundersgyan.com$fastcgi_script_name;\n                  include         fastcgi_params;\n                       fastcgi_param QUERY_STRING $query_string;\n                       fastcgi_param REQUEST_METHOD $request_method;\n                       fastcgi_param CONTENT_TYPE $content_type;\n                       fastcgi_param CONTENT_LENGTH $content_length;\n                       fastcgi_param SCRIPT_NAME $fastcgi_script_name;\n                       fastcgi_param REQUEST_URI $request_uri;\n                       fastcgi_param DOCUMENT_URI $document_uri;\n                       fastcgi_param DOCUMENT_ROOT $document_root;\n                       fastcgi_param SERVER_PROTOCOL $server_protocol;\n                       fastcgi_param GATEWAY_INTERFACE CGI/1.1;\n                       fastcgi_param SERVER_SOFTWARE nginx/$nginx_version;\n                       fastcgi_param REMOTE_ADDR $remote_addr;\n                       fastcgi_param REMOTE_PORT $remote_port;\n                      fastcgi_param SERVER_ADDR $server_addr;\n                      fastcgi_param SERVER_PORT $server_port;\n                      fastcgi_param SERVER_NAME $server_name;\n       }  \n\n }\n\n','','',''),(2,NULL,'Override php mail() function with Google smtp','','completed','1000',3,1,'2011-02-07','2011-02-07','2011-02-10','<div>We have a amazon aws micro instance running. We have two websites on the instance which are php based. We wish to over-ride the default mail() function used by php by our custom function</div>\r\n<br/>\r\n\r\n<div>We are not sure but it seems the default mail() function uses sendmail on the server & for that, there needs to be a mail server installed. We do not want to do that. We have google apps account for both the websites & want to relay the mail via the google smtp server.</div><br/>\r\n\r\n<div>For example, any mail going from <a href=\"www.cofoundersgyan.com\">www.cofoundersgyan.com</a> need to be sent via google server as going from admin@cofoundersgyan.com . Similarly, any mail going from www.stalkninja.com would need to go from google as mail from admin@stalkninja.com</div><br/>\r\n\r\n<p>I suggest two ways the problem can be done. You may select your wa7</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The path to sendmail is specified in php.ini . You can change the path to point to one of your script. You would need to figure out what parameters are being passed to sendmail & in what order. You would then need to use the parameter to send mail via google smtp. Check http://jetpackweb.com/blog/2009/07/18/override-phps-mail-function-during-development/ where the author has tried over-riding the mail() function.</li>\r\n	<li> Alternatively, you can use the override_function http://php.net/manual/en/function.override-function.php & override the mail() function altogether. You can write a php script that uses the override function & is always gets included whenever a php script is processed. There is a way to do it via php.ini. Figure that out</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div>Following would be your deliverables\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A test script that would be just one line script calling mail() function & sending a mail to pocha.sharma@gmail.com & the mail coming from admin@cofoundersgyan.com . We would provide you the password of the account.</li>\r\n	<li>Updated progress sheet where you have told which way you have chosen & how you did it</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','System Administrator,Linux, php',' * Configuration of   Mail Function            \n\n    * I have create a file /usr/share/php/MyMail/sendmail.php and giving it execution permission using chmod +x  and\n    * both /etc/php5/cli/php.ini and /etc/php5/cgi/php.ini in [mail function] section i have defined this  \n\n\nsendmail_path =  /usr/share/php/MyMail/sendmail.php\n\n    * Now edit this /usr/share/php/MyMail/sendmail.php file and specify   and  using nano editor\n    * You can use this command \n\n\n$sudo nano /usr/share/php/MyMail/sendmail.php\n           \n            after that edit that file and save it using √¢‚Ç¨≈ìctrl+O√¢‚Ç¨¬ù and close                 using √¢‚Ç¨≈ìctrl+X√¢‚Ç¨¬ù\n							','','',''),(4,NULL,'Webpage with a form, its submission handling & google chart generation from output files.','','completed','7000',10,2,'2011-02-23','2011-03-01','2011-03-10','<pre>\r\n--------------------------\r\nProject description updated on Feb 24 5:16 PM\r\n---------------------------\r\nThis project is to create a webpage with a form which when submitted, runs a command to generate some output files, create a charts from the output files & show it to the user. \r\n\r\nPlease check the attached document to view the flow of pages. You would be provided access to my server where you can do the development & show me the progress. You are free to use any language of choice - ASP.NET, PHP, Python, Java - whatever you want to work with.\r\n\r\nYou may like to read MainDocument.doc in the attached file section to know the exact requirement\r\n</pre>\r\n','Any web programming, HTML, Javascript','<pre>\r\nProgress Report:\r\n\r\n1. Made a basic UI, with forms , tabs, and generating charts.\r\n\r\nAt this point of time, the theme was non compliant, the forms needed more tweaking, and IE was having issues with early initialization and generation of all charts.\r\n\r\nThe following are then things that are going on:\r\n\r\n1. How to nicely fit huge descriptions into a form , which has more than 30 fields in one page.\r\n2. Php script to receive all form varialbes and dump them into respective files\r\n3. Trying out late implimentation and generation of charts for IE.This may be a bit irritating for the user, as each time clicking on navigation will need a chart generation first, but might just work for IE.\r\n\r\nProgress Report 2 :\r\n\r\nThe Process:\r\n\r\n1. Clearly, this project needed a lot of generation of dynamic elements, starting from tabs, which were to be populated with forms, which when submitted , would create a set of charts ,to be read from files, dynamically generated from the server.\r\n\r\n2.It was much more logical to create methods for creation of GUI Elements, so the first thing that was done was , only provide the bear neceseties, like the CSS and a basic skeleton to the HTML, and leave the generation of everything on the page to javascript\r\n\r\n3.The function are such that, all they need is the data to be filled in, and they will create forms. charts, tabs, pretty much everything the user will see on the screen , dynamically.\r\n\r\n4.Combined to the above, all this was needed to be done on one single page.No refreshes.\r\n\r\nImplementation:\r\n\r\nLibraries I have used :\r\n\r\n1. jquery : jquery.com/\r\n2. jquery form plugin : jquery.malsup.com/form/\r\n3. jquery validation plugin docs.jquery.com/Plugins/validation\r\n4. self built libraries\r\n\r\nDetails :\r\n\r\nSelf Build Libraries:\r\n\r\nFile :nativaCode.js\r\n\r\ncreateSelectFormField(‚Äútitle1‚Äù,[optionsArray1],[enabledArray1],‚Äùtitle2‚Äù,[optionsArray2],[enabledArray2]) :\r\nThis function takes care of create form fields like the ones in Data Set 2 (Bdata).Which have a drop down list.The optionsArray is the array of the options, and the enabledArray is an array which corresponds to which options are enabled.\r\nThis function in turn calls getSelectBox(title,optionsArray,enabledArray), which basically return the HTML which has to be embedded into the DOM.\r\n\r\ngetFormField(label,index,dataSet) :\r\nThis function create form fields like the ones in Dataset 1 (a) and Dataset 3(q).\r\nThe index shows , which position the value related to this field occurs in the data files (Adata.txt and Qdata.txt).\r\nE.g ‚ÄúNum Points‚Äù is a value related to Data set 3(QData)  and occurs at the second position in the file.\r\nSo a call to getFormField(\"Num points\" , 2 ,\'q\') will get you a form field, which will dump its data in Qdata.txt at the second position.\r\n\r\n\r\nshowChild(i) :Shows the related chart number.(i)\r\n\r\nIsNumeric (number) :Tells if a number in passed is numeric or not.\r\n\r\nvalidateAllFields() :\r\nCall this and it will first validate all possible fields, and if there are any violations , will show a popup box, telling the user what all data is missing.\r\n\r\nshowModal () :\r\nThis function is the magic box, where all the data is sent to the server, all charts are generated , all validation is done, and finally the user gets to see the data after calling this function.\r\nNOTE: Calling this function more than once, is not suggested.Call this function , only when you want the data to be generated and charts to be shown\r\n\r\npopulateChartWithFile(Title,XLabel,YLable,FilesArray,LegendsArray):\r\nThis is the function which really takes care of downloading a data from the generated file(from python), and converting it into charts.\r\nThe number of line series (graphs) on a chart will be equal to the number of files in FilesArray.\r\n\r\ne.g\r\npopulateChartWithFile(\"Time (s)\",  ?  Title\r\n            \"Average output voltage (V)\", ? XLabel\r\n            \"Average voltage vs time\", ? YLabel\r\n            [\'data/output13.txt\'], ? url of the file the data is in\r\n            [\'Average Voltage\']); ? Legend for the line series generated.\r\nNOTE: the number of legends === no of file in file array.\r\npopulateChartWithFile(\"log 10 (f) Frequency (Hz)\",\r\n            \"Angle(degrees)\",\r\n            \"Vo(s)/Verr(s) for Voltage source v/S Io(s)/Ierr(s)for Current source\",\r\n            [\'data/output06.txt\',\'data/output08.txt\'], ? note file array has two files.\r\n            [\'Analog\',\'Digital\']); ? note legendArray has two legends.\r\nThis function will take data from output06.txt and put it as Analog\r\nand will take data from output08.txt and put it as Digital\r\n\r\nNOTE:This can be extended to any number of files and legends.\r\n\r\n\r\nSERVER SIDE:\r\n\r\nfiles.php :\r\nTakes care of dumping data from Dataset1, Dataset 2 and Dataset3 into AData.txt, BData.txt and QData.txt\r\n\r\nfileSave.php :\r\nDumps Simulation1 , Simulation2 and Simulation3 .txt\r\n\r\ndownloadZip :\r\nThis file takes care of zipping all the files needed, and allowing the user to download all the output files in zip format as one single file.\r\n\r\nThere is a variable\r\n$files_to_zip = array(\r\n \'data/output12.txt\',\r\n \'data/simulation1.txt\',\r\n \'data/simulation2.txt\',\r\n \'data/simulation3.txt\',\r\n \'Adata.txt\', ? These files are not the ones uploaded,the files are uploaded at ‚Äò/data/Adata.txt‚Äô\r\n \'Bdata.txt\', ? These files are not the ones uploaded,the files are uploaded at ‚Äò/data/Bdata.txt‚Äô\r\n \'Qdata.txt\', ? These files are not the ones uploaded,the files are uploaded at ‚Äò/data/Qdata.txt‚Äô\r\n);\r\n.Add to this list, all files you want to send to the user as a zip.\r\n</pre>\r\n','\r\nFollowing would be your deliverables :-\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>A page which shows the form containing 60 parameters grouped in 3 categorical blocks where user can navigate between the groups using next/previous button. </li>\r\n<li>A script that handles the submitted data from the form, dumps the data to appropriate files, runs a provided command.</li>\r\n<li>A final page which shows google charts generated from the files created by running a command. All the generated files & some pre-loaded static files need to be zipped & a link to be shown for downloading it.</li>\r\n<li>Error handling needs to be done on the form page. All fields are compulsory & form should not submit if any of the fields remain empty.  Post submission if the given command throws an error, the user stays on the form page with all the form fields filled with values before submission. The error need to be shown on top of the form page.</li>\r\n<li>Once done, transfer all the files to my server using ftp (I would give you the login) & show the complete system working. </li>\r\n</ol>','The google chart generation is a tricky part in the project. \r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Create a page with form where I can upload a text file with values in the form (x,y) one below another. Check attached file output01.txt</li>\r\n	<li>On submission of the form, another page should come up which should show a chart plotted from the file I uploaded</li>\r\n	<li>Upload the page & the backend script on your server & pass on the link so that I can test it myself</li>\r\n<li>If you do not have serve space, get some free space at http://x10hosting.com</li>\r\n</ul>',''),(5,NULL,' Android project for pros & beginners alike - Create a database helper file','','completed','1000',5,3,'2011-03-06','2011-03-17','2011-03-22','<pre>\r\n--------------------------------\r\nUpdate on March 10, 8:28 PM\r\n\r\nA bug has been discovered in TestSqliteHelper.java file. It was using SqliteDB class to instantiate SqliteDBObj, while the class to be used is SqliteHelper. We have updated the file. Please use the new file. If you still see the old file, remove browser cache & refresh. All those who had problem compiling the code can now try it.\r\n-------------------------------------\r\n\r\nSeasoned Android programmers may jump to Task section. Rest please read on\r\n\r\nAndroid device comes equipped with Sqlite database & this project is to create a helper file which acts as wrapper over the database functions. The database functions are here <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://developer.android.com/reference/android/database/sqlite/SQLiteDatabase.html\">http://developer.android.com/reference/android/database/sqlite/SQLiteDatabase.html</a> . To see (but not to get daunted) as to how a sample helper file would look, check the attachment BdayDbAdapter.java\r\n\r\nBefore you go ahead & attempt the task, you need to be up & running a hello world on Android SDK. Attached the two documents to get yourself going. How to quick start with Android.docx is provided by the project creator while Steps to install SDK.docx document steps which a non-Androider 3rd year student Soumitra followed to got up & running in record 3 hours :)\r\n</pre>\r\nSome probable issues you might run into :-\r\n<ul>\r\n        <li>If you are behind a proxy (if you are using your college internet) then the SDK Manager would create problem. Check the comment at the blog regarding editing android.bat <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://bharathi.posterous.com/install-android-sdk-thru-proxy-with-authentic\">http://bharathi.posterous.com/install-android-sdk-thru-proxy-with-authentic</a> .\r\n<blockquote>After much messing around, I managed to get this working really easily.\r\nEdit android.bat, and in the call to java.exe, insert the following parameters VM parameters before -jar\r\n-Dhttp.proxyUsername=\"username\" -Dhttp.proxyPassword=\"password\"\r\nNote that there\'s no space between D and http. You still need to put in the host/port in the settings. </blockquote>\r\n If there is a better way that you have figured out, please let us know in the comment section.</li>\r\n	<li>A serious pain in the a$$ for first timers is choice of ADT. As project creator has mentioned, stick to 1.5 or 2.1 version of platform, we say the same. Just dont use the 3.0 version. It did not work for us. Quite a few first timers were stuck here for quite sometime</li>\r\n	<li>For the naive java programmers like us, we realized that Activity name should match the Class name of your main function. For example - if you specified HelloAndroid as Activity name in Eclipse while creating the project, you also made sure that the main file & function is named HelloAndroid.java & HelloAndroid respectively</li>\r\n	<li>There are chances that you would be hit with most frustrating run-time errors - the app quit unexpectedly. LogCat is the real savior in those situation. Search it in your Eclipse or launch it on your command prompt by typing - adb logcat. abd is located in SDK directory/platform-tools</li>\r\n</ul>','Some java, Bit of SQL, Loads of patience, Android is bonus','','The actual project is on similar lines of the contest. Check Task.docx. A refined doc would be given to the task winner with all db schema.\r\n<p style=\"font-size: small; font-style:italic\">This project cum contest is being created by we non-seasoned-Android cum Admin guys who picked it all up in 1 day to make sure all the task is pickable. If you are seasoned guy & has something to point which should change the approach, feel free to comment in discussion board & we would be happy to do it</p>','Well, no hurries please. Before you start with it- please read the two links so that you understand what you gonna deal with it. You do not have to read it the textbook style - just a cursory glance & back here\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Sample code implementing Sqlite handling in Android - http://marakana.com/forums/android/examples/55.html</li>\r\n	<li>Database Open Helper file reference - http://developer.android.com/reference/android/database/sqlite/SQLiteOpenHelper.html</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Create a new project with name TestSqliteHelper. Choose package - stalkninja.sqlitehelper. It would create a project with TestSqliteHelper.java as the main file. Overwrite it with the attached file TestSqliteHelper.java. Also copy attached SqliteHelper.java inside src/stalkninja/sqlitehelper. Convince Eclipse if it growns. Run the project to make sure you got all the settings right.</li>\r\n	<li> Read up TestSqliteHelper.java. The onCreate function is the main entry point. It calls certain functions from SqliteHelper.java. You do NOT have to change anything in this file. Just read it, understand the flow & move on.</li>\r\n	<li> Move to SqliteHelper.java. There are various placeholders (places left empty with pointers) where you need to write the code. There are appropriate hints in the file itself.</li>\r\n	<li> Once everything is done & you got it all running - take a snapshot of your emulator which would be showing your name & email (check emulator.png in attachment), upload it on picasa, facebook, your server or anywhere & paste the link in the discussion board. Send the code to admin@stalkninja.com. <span style=\"color:black\">Do not put actual code or link to your source code in discussion board.</span>. Pat yourself at the back as you are done</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"color:black\">Remember, the lines of code you need to write would NOT grow beyond 10 lines. So read more & write less :)</span>\r\n<h3>Tip</h3>\r\n<blockquote> A bad habit for newbies is to code it all & then test it all. Do not do that. For eg. - write the code for database creation & then check if the database & table are being created by running the code. Then move to insert & select queries.\r\nThere are times that Eclipse would behave erratically & groans like anything. Either refresh the project or simply restart Eclipse. It should make both you & Eclipse happy. </blockquote>\r\n\r\nThe project creator would select one person from the task doers. The criteria being -\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>How much you understand what you doing - quite subjective, but we would gauge :)</li>\r\n	<li>How well written your code is. Well there is small part, but we would make it out</li>\r\n	<li>How responsive you would be to the queries put up by project creator on the discussion board</li>\r\n	<li>How well you play the guitar .. well just kidding</li>\r\n</ol>',''),(7,NULL,'Product Catalogue website development','Too low a budget for the work desired. Lack of sufficient pointers in the description.','cancelled','INR 2500',2,5,'2011-03-10',NULL,NULL,'<pre>\r\nThe website to be cloned is http://www.abcweddings.com\r\n\r\nThe menu item Online Store @  http://www.abc.weddingstar.com/ is not needed. \r\n\r\nThe display of Catagories and Products has to be similar if not same. The client needs a back end to add products easily and customize the products categories. You are free to use any CMS as long as the work can be done.\r\n\r\nPlease consider the following points \r\n\r\nThe product entry should be easy (preferably like in Wordpress) \r\nAdding thumnails to a category should be customizable...\r\nThis is only a product catalogue and not a shopping cart. \r\nPlease put a query form / contact form below every product so that the query for Sale can be directly mailed to the admin\r\nYou may use one of the shopping cart utilities available in wordpress ex: http://shopperpress.com\r\n</pre>','php, css, cms (wordpress or joomla or some other similar cms) ',NULL,'<pre>\r\nA clone of the above mentioned website\r\n\r\nCMS based backend to insert products / product categories and content \r\n\r\nBack end to edit  / add / delete a category and product(s) \r\n</pre>\r\n','',''),(8,NULL,'Javascript chart plotting using gRapahel or Graphico','The budget for the project was low.','cancelled','1000',7,6,'2011-03-14',NULL,NULL,'<pre>\r\nWe need to plot charts on our web page for which we have figured out two javascript libraries \r\n\r\n1. gRapahel - http://g.raphaeljs.com/\r\n2. Grafico - http://grafico.kilianvalkhof.com/documentation/index.html\r\n\r\nDocumentation of gRaphael - https://github.com/kennyshen/g.raphael\r\n\r\nYou need to research into it & tell us which of it is better (give us good reason) & then implement the chosen library.\r\n</pre>','Javascript, JSON',NULL,'<pre>\r\n1) Javascript file that can be included in an HTML page. The file has a function which takes a 2 DIMENSIONAL json variable as input (check attached monthly_return.txt & d.json.txt) & plots the chart WITH LABELS. Another input parameter decide what kind of chart it would be - pie, line or bar chart. Please see the embedded excel documents in the file. They are clear w.r.t. data and the output required. (Please ask questions)\r\n\r\n2) An HTML file which has the previous javascript file included & a field to upload a json file (see attached file) & chart type to be selected. On upload & submit, the appropriate chart should show up.\r\n\r\nFor Chart 3 (Dynamically refreshing Line Chart) (refer project specs):\r\n3.	This is the same as chart 1 (see doc). Only additions are:\r\n3.1.	AJAX calls to php files to query the database to get JSON data.\r\n3.2.	Push data into the JSON / Chart object to dynamically show the chart progress with time. (see poll for data example here. http://people.iola.dk/olau/flot/examples/ajax.html)\r\n3.3.	Deliverables are:\r\n3.3.1.	Define database table same as the json data (This is the same as the Line Chart Data.csv attached). Simply import it into MySQL. I can do it using Toad on my machine.\r\n3.3.2.	Write PHP code to output data for the AJAX call.\r\n3.3.3.	Write Javascript call to deliver the charting functionality.\r\n</pre>','<pre>\r\nPlot the exact bar chart as in the Project Spec.docx. Take the screen-shot of your plot & put it on discussion board. Send the code to admin@stalkninja.com . \r\n\r\nIgnore the legend of years on the right side of the chart.\r\n\r\nBonus tip: Additional weight-age would be given who create a clutter-free graph, hover-effect etc. Mention such attributes if not visible on the screen-shot, in the comment with the screen-shot.  \r\n\r\nMAKE SURE YOU DO NOT POST THE SOURCE CODE OR LINK TO THE HTML PAGE SHOWING THE CHART ON THE DISCUSSION BOARD, as those who do not know, the source code of javascript is visible on the browser.\r\n</pre>',''),(9,NULL,'Android barcode scanner application','The project can not be done with the information given. It is lot complex.','cancelled','3000',30,7,'2011-03-15',NULL,NULL,'<pre>\r\nThe project should not take more than 3-4 days of coding. We have put 30 days to ensure that the project does not conflict with the studies of the Ninja.\r\n\r\nThe application should be able to \r\n1. Scan the barcode on any book. See here an example code to do the same. http://www.mattcutts.com/blog/android-barcode-scanner/ This is just an example. You may use your own code.\r\n2. Call a url on mysmartprice with the isbn number as input.\r\n3. The url will provide an xml file with relevant information. (this will be done by me)\r\n4. Extract the relevant information from the xml and display it to user.\r\n</pre>','basic knowledge about android application development',NULL,'The android application source code that will be able to do steps given above.','Create hello world android application. The application should accept name of the person as an input and output hello name.',''),(11,NULL,'registeration login/passwd form','','open','3000',5,2,'2011-03-24',NULL,NULL,'<p>I have a web based application that runs on a server.</p>\r\n<p>I need to create a user sign up/ login /passwd form.</p>\r\n<p>The user goes to my website and then gets directed to sign in/login page.</p>\r\n<p>From there, the user needs to be able to login/passwd + image verification like an image of 2+2&nbsp; and he enters 4 to validate. (To make sure there is a human sitting behind the computer)</p>\r\n<p>The code is written in php&nbsp; + python. The user enters some parameters in a form and the code generates some files and displays some plots. Right now the program doesnt support multi users.</p>\r\n<p>The idea is to be able to support multiple users access the stuff @ the same time.</p>\r\n<p>So the files need to be written in mutiple login name based directories.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>Also an entry with feedback/comments/questions/ that can get dumped in a file or send an email will be great.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p></p>','let u decide',NULL,'<p>1. A login/registeration/forgot passwd , image verification based form..(only human logins)</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>2. When a user registers , A disclaimer image with a check box showing up after that where users accept / reject.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>3. A look and feel like this expected <a href=\"http://recruiterbox.com/accounts/login\">http://recruiterbox.com/accounts/login<br /></a></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>4. Once the user logs in, chartupload should show http://50.56.94.159/chartUpload/prototype.html</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>5. The user is expected to enter data . The web app dumps data in to files. right now the paths are hard coded. That data needs to be dumped into ...../login/......so each login will have a seperate directory .</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>6.&nbsp; the backend code generates some data and writes some files . These also have to be written in the /login directory. The backend code is confidential so the ninja will have to demonstrate it with a dummy python code that will take the login info and write some files in /login directory . The web app calls a python script once all data has been dumped so it can be passed as a parameter.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>7. http://recruiterbox.com/contact_us</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>type contact us form is also required. This should send a message to consulting@controltrix.com email address.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p></p>','<p>The task is included in the deliverables.</p>\r\n<p>I am open to hearing better ideas from expert ninjas...</p>','ac3d53168d36334f2ce137f117cc4ed1');
