INSERT INTO `Review` VALUES (1,NULL,1,1,1,'<p>Amit had done a good job. He did quite a bit of research & figured out the solution to the problems himself.</p>\r\n<p>There was a slight delay in completion of the project because of his placements & my sudden travel plan, but Amit covered for that.</p>\r\n<p>Amit is slightly lacking in his communication skills but his problem solving skills are great. I am sure his communication skills would improve over time.</p>','This was my first commercial server configuration project which one on Amazon EC2. I got great experience working with Mr. Ashish sharma. He is very helpful and trusted.',9.00,10.00),(2,NULL,2,1,1,'<p>Amit did a good job again this time. He needed some pointers, but winded up job as expected.</p>','Excellent and trusted startuper  ',10.00,10.00),(3,'2011-03-24 14:04:53',4,2,14,'<p>Neeraj did a great job considering the unknown limitations of free softwares . He was very accomodative of most requests and took great initiative to figure out and research things out himself.  He went out of way on several occasions.\r\nThe complexity exceeded my expectations and Neeraj solved plenty of problems on the way. Nice to see that such things do work....\r\nAshish gave great help too in ironing out things..</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Perhaps you guys should also undertake research/ figuring out projects... for the non tech dummies...Where the outcome/pitfalls are uncertain but you get paid nevertheless e.g. how to plot x and y independently zoomable plot on google charts... </p>','The project deliverable were clearly defined , at the same time,  lot of freedom was given on what technologies can be used. My constantly changing prototypes were well received , with again a clear set of goals being drafted for the next iteration.Anusheel has been very patient as well as helpful and forthcoming through and through.A fair amount of self-restraint was shown, so as not to gloat the project deliverable during the project, which certainly has been a plus plus throughout.\r\nAnusheel , was nonchalant even if my code had glitches and incompleteness sometimes.This certainly helped me to  work constantly  towards improving the quality of the code, without fear of experimenting on the way.\r\nSo overall, controltrix has been a nice experience for me.',9.00,9.00);
